p%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Fed%20also%20said%20it%20would%20assess%20a%20range%20of%20data%20points%20%26quot%3Bin%20determining%20the%20extent%20of%20additional%20policy%20firming%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20indicates%20that%20officials%20see%20the%20possibility%20of%20more%20monetary%20tightening%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20reporters%20after%20the%20decision%20was%20announced%2C%20Fed%20chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20insisted%20that%20no%20decision%20has%20been%20taken%20to%20hike%20at%20every%20other%20meeting%2C%20as%20some%20analysts%20have%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20going%20to%20be%20going%20meeting%20by%20meeting%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20Fed%20would%20continue%20to%20adopt%20a%20%26quot%3Bdata-dependent%26quot%3B%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Long%20way%20to%20go'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20previous%20FOMC%20meeting%20in%20June%2C%20the%20median%20forecast%20was%20for%20two%20additional%20rate%20hikes%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20quarter%20percentage-point%20rise%2C%20which%20was%20in%20line%20with%20analysts'%20expectations%2C%20is%20the%20Fed's%2011th%20since%20it%20began%20an%20aggressive%20campaign%20of%20monetary%20tightening%20last%20March%20in%20response%20to%20rising%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20inflation%20has%20continued%20to%20fall%20since%20the%20decision%20in%20June%20to%20pause%20rate%20hikes%2C%20it%20remains%20above%20the%20Fed's%20long-term%20target%20of%20two%20percent%20--%20suggesting%20more%20policy%20action%20may%20be%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnemployment%20has%20remained%20close%20to%20historic%20lows%2C%20while%20economic%20growth%20for%20the%20first%20quarter%20was%20revised%20up%20sharply%20on%20resilient%20consumer%20spending%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInflation%20has%20moderated%20somewhat%20since%20the%20middle%20of%20last%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Powell%20said%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNonetheless%2C%20the%20process%20of%20getting%20inflation%20back%20down%20to%20two%20percent%20has%20a%20long%20way%20to%20go%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESoft%20landing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20positive%20economic%20news%20has%20increased%20the%20chances%20of%20a%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bsoft%20landing%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20the%20Fed%20succeeds%20in%20bringing%20down%20inflation%20by%20raising%20interest%20rates%20while%20avoiding%20a%20recession%20and%20a%20surge%20in%20joblessness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20Powell%20reiterated%20that%20he%20felt%20a%20soft%20landing%20is%20still%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20has%20been%20my%20view%20consistently%20that%20we%20do%20have%20a%20shot%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BThat's%20been%20my%20view%2C%20that's%20still%20my%20view.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPowell%20told%20reporters%20that%20his%20staff's%20expectations%20for%20a%20recession%20to%20start%20later%20this%20year%20has%20diminished%2C%20as%20more%20positive%20economic%20data%20has%20come%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20staff%20now%20has%20a%20noticeable%20slowdown%20in%20growth%20starting%20later%20this%20year%20in%20the%20forecast%2C%20but%20given%20the%20resilience%20of%20the%20economy%20recently%2C%20they%20are%20no%20longer%20forecasting%20a%20recession%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20investors%20had%20more%20or%20less%20priced%20in%20a%20hike%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20they%20have%20been%20less%20confident%20about%20the%20chances%20of%20another%20increase%20at%20the%20next%20Fed%20meeting%20in%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFutures%20traders%20currently%20assign%20a%20probability%20of%20just%20over%2020%20percent%20that%20the%20FOMC%20will%20raise%20rates%20again%20in%20September%2C%20according%20to%20CME%20Group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%