s.%20It%20comes%20in%20a%2040mm%20case%20size%20and%20the%20screen%20is%20slightly%20smaller%20at%201.1%20inches.%20It's%20not%20drastic%20but%20it%20would%20make%20a%20difference.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThankfully%2C%20the%20band%20that%20comes%20with%20the%20Venu%202%20is%20a%20different%20story.%20With%20tons%20of%20sizing%20slots%20and%20a%20soft%20silicone%20material%2C%20it's%20a%20far%20cry%20in%20terms%20of%20comfort%20compared%20to%20the%20watch%20face.%20Plus%2C%20there%20are%20over%2040%20band%20options%20you%20can%20purchase%20via%20Garmin%20if%20you%20want%20to%20customize%20your%20look.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20shot%20of%20a%20person%20holding%20the%20Garmin%20Venu%202%20fitness%20tracker%20to%20showcase%20the%20side%20buttons%20and%20watch%20strap.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c12479671ed600191572c3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222274%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EShannon%20Ullman%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20display%20itself%20is%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20mixed%20bag.%20It%20does%20have%20an%20impressive%20resolution%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20Garmin's%20first%20AMOLED%20display%2C%20after%20all%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it's%20a%20little%20difficult%20to%20navigate%2C%20especially%20for%20first-time%20users.%20There%20are%20just%20two%20side%20buttons%20(the%20Venu%202%20Plus%20offers%20three)%2C%20and%20it%20takes%20some%20practice%20to%20understand%20how%20to%20operate%20each%20one.%20I%20accidentally%20started%20a%20strength-training%20workout%20more%20times%20than%20I%20can%20count.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20health%20tracking%20is%20your%20main%20priority%2C%20you'll%20like%20how%20accessible%20your%20stats%20are.%20Simply%20swiping%20up%20gives%20you%20a%20full%20picture%20of%20your%20daily%20activity%2C%20sleep%20patterns%2C%20and%20heart%20rate.%20However%2C%20I%20did%20still%20find%20myself%20checking%20the%20Garmin%20Connect%20App%20for%20data%20more%20than%20the%20actual%20watch%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Activity%20tracking%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20workout%20builder%20is%20great%20for%20DIY%20athletes%20and%20gym%20newbies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20shot%20of%20a%20Garmin%20Venu%202%E2%80%99s%20watch%20face%20showing%20a%20heart%20rate%20reading.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c1253d1f17bb00196e6f58%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222274%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EShannon%20Ullman%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Venu%202%20excels%20as%20a%20fitness%20tracker%2C%20particularly%20regarding%20the%20workout%20builder%20that%20allows%20you%20to%20create%20a%20routine%20in%20the%20Garmin%20Connect%20app%20and%20then%20download%20it%20to%20the%20watch%20for%20easy%20access.%20There%20are%20also%20tons%20of%20pre-existing%20workouts%20within%20the%20app%20you%20can%20pull%20from%2C%20and%20the%20watch%20even%20displays%20animated%20images%20of%20each%20move%20for%20you%20to%20follow%20along.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20enjoyed%20the%20tracking%20and%20workout%20creation%20features%20on%20my%20lift%20days%2C%20I%20didn't%20find%20much%20use%20for%20the%20other%20exercise%20options.%20I%20thought%20the%20HITT%20activity%20would%20be%20perfect%20for%20my%20HITT%20workout%20class%20but%20the%20constant%20starting%20and%20stopping%20of%20the%20timer%20made%20it%20more%20of%20a%20hassle%20than%20an%20aid.%20Over%20time%2C%20I%20just%20used%20the%20cardio%20option%2C%20which%20at%20least%20kept%20my%20heart%20rate%20levels%20and%20how%20many%20calories%20I%20burned%20in%20check.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20feature%20that%20makes%20the%20Venu%202%20especially%20worth%20wearing%20is%20its%20built-in%20GPS.%20I'm%20not%20a%20runner%2C%20but%20did%20use%20it%20while%20on%20long%20walks%20with%20my%20pup.%20I%20found%20it%20to%20be%20highly%20accurate%2C%20which%20is%20a%20major%20plus%20for%20anyone%20intending%20to%20meticulously%20track%20their%20workouts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20built-in%20personal%20running%20coach%20(which%20is%20free%20when%20you%20buy%20the%20watch)%20also%20makes%20it%20a%20decent%20option%20for%20aspiring%20marathoners.%20Just%20know%20that%20if%20you%20plan%20on%20regularly%20using%20the%20GPS%20and%20the%20music%2C%20it%20does%20whittle%20the%20battery%20life%20down%20from%20five%20days%20to%20just%20six%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20didn't%20have%20access%20to%20test%20the%20watch's%20supposed%205%20ATM%20water%20rating%20(an%20abbreviation%20of%20atmosphere%2C%20meaning%20it's%20waterproof%20up%20to%2050-meter%20depths)%2C%20it%20did%20hold%20up%20fine%20in%20the%20shower.%20That%20alone%20makes%20it%20a%20quality%20contender%20for%20anyone%20looking%20to%20track%20their%20swimming%20workouts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Health%20features%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFeatures%20advanced%20health%20tracking%20with%20useful%20insights%20for%20hardcore%20or%20casual%20athletes%20alike%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person's%20hand%20holding%20the%20Garmin%20Venu%202%20fitness%20tracker%20with%20its%20underside%20facing%20up%2C%20showing%20off%20its%20sensors.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c126271f17bb00196e70e1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EShannon%20Ullman%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20shortage%20of%20information%20the%20Venu%202%20provides%20about%20your%20health%20as%20it%20can%20track%20your%20steps%2C%20calories%20burned%2C%20hydration%2C%20stress%2C%20sleep%2C%20blood%20oxygen%2C%20menstrual%20cycle%2C%20and%20respiration%2C%20among%20others.%20Some%20of%20it%20does%20require%20manual%20entry%20(like%20hydration%20tracking)%2C%20but%20most%20of%20the%20analysis%20and%20tracking%20is%20automatic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20most%20similar%20wearables%2C%20the%20more%20you%20wear%20it%2C%20the%20more%20insights%20you'll%20receive.%20For%20instance%2C%20it%20offers%20new%2C%20holistic%20health%20tracking%20for%20stress%20levels%20and%20sleep%20patterns.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20these%20sounded%20great%20in%20theory%2C%20I%20did%20find%20it%20hard%20to%20wear%20the%20Venu%202%20for%20prolonged%20periods%20of%20time%20due%20to%20the%20uncomfortable%20watch%20face%2C%20and%20the%20insights%20weren't%20compelling%20enough%20for%20me%20to%20stick%20it%20out.%20It%20was%20nice%20to%20have%20my%20cycle%20monitored%20but%20the%20tracking%20wasn't%20nearly%20as%20comprehensive%20as%20some%20of%20the%20other%20apps%20I%20use%20on%20my%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20wearing%20the%20Venu%202%20for%20a%20few%20days%2C%20it%20compiles%20all%20your%20amassed%20data%20and%20creates%20what%20Garmin%20calls%20your%20Body%20Battery.%20The%20Body%20Battery%20is%20a%20combination%20of%20your%20resting%20heart%20rate%2C%20stress%20levels%2C%20and%20other%20factors%20that%20give%20you%20an%20overall%20measurement%20of%20your%20body's%20energy%20reserves%20between%201%20and%20100.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20the%20higher%20your%20battery%2C%20the%20more%20energy%20you%20have.%20I%20found%20this%20to%20be%20an%20especially%20helpful%20feature%20when%20deciding%20what%20kind%20of%20workout%20I%20should%20do%20on%20any%20given%20day%2C%20and%20whether%20I%20should%20push%20myself%20or%20take%20it%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Smartwatch%20capability%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20offers%20basic%20smartwatch%20capability%20plus%20the%20ability%20to%20store%20and%20play%20music%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223023%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Garmin%20Venu%202%20fitness%20tracker%20on%20a%20person's%20wrist%20showing%20a%20screen%20with%20various%20smartwatch%20features.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c126d3671ed6001915775e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EShannon%20Ullman%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20best%20features%20of%20the%20Venu%202%20is%20that%20it%20offers%20music%20storage%20capabilities%2C%20allowing%20you%20to%20download%20playlists%20and%20songs%20from%20either%20Spotify%2C%20Deezer%2C%20or%20Amazon%20Music.%20While%20you%20can't%20access%20your%20entire%20library%20via%20the%20watch%2C%20you%20can%20at%20least%20put%20your%20favorite%20workout%20tunes%20in%20one%20place%20for%20easy%20listening.%20Plus%2C%20this%20means%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20tote%20your%20phone%20along%20on%20a%20run.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20smartwatch%2C%20the%20Venu%202%20is%20quite%20basic.%20It%20gets%20app%20notifications%2C%20as%20well%20as%20alerts%20for%20calls%20and%20texts%2C%20but%20only%20Android%20users%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20respond%20to%20messages%20(iPhone%20users%20still%20get%20the%20notifications%20but%20that's%20it).%20If%20you%20opt%20for%20the%20Venu%202%20Plus%2C%20you'd%20then%20have%20access%20to%20a%20built-in%20microphone%20that%20allows%20you%20to%20make%20calls%20and%20receive%20%26quot%3Bvoice%20assistant%20support%26quot%3B%20via%20Bluetooth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Battery%20life%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMulti-day%20battery%20life%20is%20one%20of%20the%20Venu%202's%20highlights%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBattery%20life%20among%20wearables%20is%20an%20incredibly%20polarizing%20feature%20as%20some%20barely%20make%20it%20through%20a%20day%20before%20needing%20a%20recharge%20while%20others%20can%20last%20upwards%20of%20five%2C%20six%2C%20or%20seven%20days.%20The%20Venu%202%20falls%20in%20the%20latter%20category%2C%20with%20a%20maximum%20battery%20life%20of%20roughly%20five%20days%20(so%20long%20as%20the%20GPS%20and%20music%20capability%20aren't%20always%20on).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20you%20do%20use%20the%20tracking%20features%20and%20the%20music%20playback%20normally%2C%20you%20can%20still%20expect%20to%20get%20several%20days%20of%20battery%20life%20out%20of%20the%20watch.%20Plus%2C%20once%20it%20does%20finally%20die%2C%20it%20never%20took%20more%20than%20an%20hour%20or%20so%20to%20fully%20recharge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Should%20you%20buy%20it%3F%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EShould%20you%20buy%20it%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20in%20the%20market%20for%20a%20wearable%20that%20offers%20advanced%20health%20metrics%20and%20accurate%20fitness%20tracking%2C%20the%20Venu%202%20is%20highly%20worth%20considering.%20Though%20its%20bulky%20design%20may%20not%20be%20for%20everyone%2C%20it%20is%20available%20in%20smaller%20sizes%20via%20Garmin%2C%20so%20folks%20with%20smaller%20wrists%20shouldn't%20be%20entirely%20dissuaded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20doesn't%20offer%20the%20latest%20smartwatch%20capabilities%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20watch%20that's%20made%20entirely%20for%20the%20active%20crowd%20and%20is%20even%20a%20solid%20choice%20for%20first-time%20wearers%20or%20those%20just%20beginning%20their%20fitness%20journey%20(though%20the%20learning%20curve%20for%20navigating%20the%20watch%20is%20quite%20steep).%20Overall%2C%20its%20comprehensive%20approach%20to%20health%2C%20wellness%2C%20and%20fitness%20makes%20it%20a%20valuable%20asset%20for%20anyone%20looking%20to%20stay%20in%20shape.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fgarmin-venu-2-review%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690405485000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c143ff35e9130019c65da7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fgarmin-venu-2-review%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Garmin's%20Venu%202%20is%20a%20large%20wearable%20with%20basic%20smartwatch%20function%2C%20GPS%2C%20and%20insightful%20health%20features%20like%20stress%2C%20sleep%2C%20and%20hydration%20tracking.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Shannon%20Ullman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fgarmin-venu-2-review%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22ASI%20says%20survey%20won%E2%80%99t%20damage%20Gyanvapi%3B%20order%20likely%20today%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690405342000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102149877%2Cimgsize-131094.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fvaranasi%2Fasi-says-survey-wont-damage-gyanvapi-mosque-allahabad-high-court-order-likely-today%2Farticleshow%2F102149878.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20ASI%20assured%20the%20Allahabad%20HC%20through%20an%20affidavit%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20no%20damage%20would%20be%20caused%20to%20the%20structure%20due%20to%20methods%20used%20for%20the%20survey%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20complex%20as%20per%20the%20order%20of%20the%20Varanasi%20district%20judge.%20CJ%20Pritinker%20Diwaker%2C%20hearing%20a%20petition%20by%20AIM%20challenging%20the%20Varanasi%20court%E2%80%99s%20July%2021%20order%20for%20a%20scientific%20survey%20of%20the%20mosque%20premises%2C%20deferred%20the%20hearing%20till%203.30pm%20on%20Thursday%2C%20when%20it%20is%20likely%20to%20pronounce%20judgment%2C%20and%20asked%20the%20ASI%20not%20to%20carry%20out%20any%20survey.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22RAJESH%20KUMAR%20PANDEY%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fvaranasi%2Fasi-says-survey-wont-damage-gyanvapi-mosque-allahabad-high-court-order-likely-today%2Farticleshow%2F102149878.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20US%20military%20once%20detonated%20a%20nuclear%20bomb%20directly%20above%20the%20heads%20of%205%20officers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225001%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20military%20Private%20First%20Class%20Jack%20Wilson%20(left%2C%20fore)%20and%20Sergeant%20Glenn%20Poth%20(right%2C%20fore)%20look%20at%20the%20smoke%20plume%20of%20a%20nuclear%20detonation%20as%20part%20of%20Operation%20Tumbler-Snapper%20at%20the%20Nevada%20Proving%20Grounds%2C%20Nevada%2C%20early%20to%20mid%201952.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c16fe642834d00193e5ec6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223784%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20five%20men%20weren't%20required%20%E2%80%94%20%E2%80%94%20to%20stand%20under%20the%20explosion%2C%20which%2C%20unlike%20the%20one%20pictured%20here%2C%20would%20have%20been%20in%20the%20air%2C%20about%20three%20miles%20up.%3Cp%3EPhotoQuest%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%201957%2C%20the%20US%20military%20conducted%20an%20test%20of%20an%20unguided%20nuclear%20rocket.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFive%20Air%20Force%20officers%20reportedly%20volunteered%20to%20stand%20directly%20underneath%20the%20test.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAll%20five%20men%20are%20said%20to%20have%20later%20developed%20cancer.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20history%20of%20US%20nuclear%20testing%20is%20full%20of%20bad%20ideas%2C%20and%20among%20them%20is%20undoubtedly%20five%20US%20military%20men%20standing%20at%20ground%20zero%20during%20an%20atmospheric%20test%20in%20the%20late%201950s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Christopher%20Nolan's%20new%20film%20%26quot%3BOppenheimer%26quot%3B%20is%20prompting%20plenty%20of%20discussion%20about%20the%20US%20military's%20early%20nuclear%20bomb%20tests%20and%20the%20effects%20of%20radiation%2C%20it%20doesn't%20capture%20in%20full%20some%20of%20the%20reckless%20oddities%20of%20nuclear%20testing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20July%2019%2C%201957%2C%20the%20Nevada%20Test%20Site%20conducted%20a%20test%20of%20an%20unguided%20nuclear%20air-to-air%20rocket.%20The%20purpose%20of%20the%20weapon%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20Genie%20%E2%80%94%20was%20to%20counter%20potential%20nuclear-armed%20Soviet%20Union%20bombers%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.popularmechanics.com%2Fmilitary%2Fweapons%2Fa21937%2Fmen-stood-under-nuclear-test-1957%2F%5C%22%3EPopular%20Mechanics%3C%2Fa%3E%20report.%20The%20test%20was%20concerned%20with%20whether%20or%20not%20the%20rocket%20could%20be%20effectively%20aimed%20at%20and%20hit%20a%20bomber%20without%20a%20guidance%20system.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENuclear%20air-to-air%20rockets%20are%20a%20questionable%20concept%2C%20but%20a%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-military-nuked-airships-with-balloon-bombs-to-test-survival-2023-2%5C%22%3Eunusual%20experiments%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20conducted%20at%20the%20Nevada%20Test%20Site%20during%20the%20early%20years%20of%20the%20Atomic%20Age.%20A%20really%20odd%20thing%20about%20this%20test%2C%20the%20%26quot%3BJohn%26quot%3B%20shot%20of%20the%20Operation%20Plumbbob%20test%20series%2C%C2%A0is%20that%20for%20some%20reason%2C%20a%20group%20of%20five%20US%20Air%20Force%20officers%20decided%20to%20plant%20themselves%20at%20ground%20zero%20of%20the%20site%2C%20standing%2018%2C500%20feet%20directly%20below%20where%20the%20Genie%20rocket%20would%20ultimately%20explode.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20men%20%E2%80%94%20identified%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Fsections%2Fkrulwich%2F2012%2F07%2F16%2F156851175%2Ffive-men-agree-to-stand-directly-under-an-exploding-nuclear-bomb%5C%22%3ENPR%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20Col.%20Sidney%20Bruce%2C%20Lt.%20Col%20Frank%20Ball%2C%20Maj.%20Normal%20%26quot%3BBodie%26quot%3B%20Bodinger%2C%20Maj.%20John%20Hughes%2C%20and%20Don%20Luttrell%20%E2%80%94%20weren't%20required%20to%20be%20involved%20in%20or%20even%20attend%20the%20test.%20Popular%20Mechanics%20reported%20they%20volunteered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it's%20not%20clear%20what%20the%20purpose%20was%2C%20a%20theory%20has%20been%20put%20forward%20that%20it%20was%20intended%20to%20help%20alleviate%20any%20concerns%20about%20nuclear%20fallout%C2%A0from%20nuclear%20air-to-air%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20clear%2C%20though%2C%20is%20how%20the%20%26quot%3BJohn%26quot%3B%20shot%20went%20down%2C%20thanks%20to%20US%20government%20footage%20shot%20by%20a%20man%20named%20George%20Yoshitake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22youtube%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FBlE1BdOAfVc%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20footage%2C%20the%20five%20men%20stand%20at%20what%20they've%20labeled%20%26quot%3BGround%20Zero%3A%20Population%205%2C%26quot%3B%20looking%20upwards%20at%20the%20F-89%20Scorpion%20interceptors%20flying%20above%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20voiceover%20countdowns%20before%20the%20Genie%20launches%20and%20explodes%2C%20causing%20a%20bright%20light%20that%20prompts%20the%20five%20men%20to%20shield%20their%20eyes.%20And%20then%20the%20sound%20of%20the%20explosion%20startles%20the%20men%20before%20the%20video%20shows%20the%20fireball%20from%20the%20nuke.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20aftermath%2C%20the%20five%20men%20shake%20hands%2C%20congratulating%20each%20other.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20only%20regrets%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Col.%20Bruce%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bare%20that%20everybody%20couldn't%20have%20been%20out%20here%20at%20ground%20zero%20with%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20%26quot%3BJohn%26quot%3B%20experiment%2C%20the%20Genie%20was%20never%20tested%20again.%20Decades%20later%2C%20civilian%20cameraman%20Yoshitake%20told%20Fox%20News%20about%20the%20incident%2C%20saying%20he%20hadn't%20volunteered%20for%20the%20shoot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20a%20call%20saying%20they%20needed%20me%20out%20for%20a%20special%20test%2C%26quot%3B%20Yoshitake%20said%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frafu.com%2F2013%2F12%2Fthe-atomic-filmmaker%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Rafu%20Shimpo%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20bilingual%20Japanese-English%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20found%20out%20when%20I%20got%20to%20Nevada%20that%20I%20was%20going%20to%20be%20standing%20at%20Ground%20Zero.%20It%20was%20going%20to%20explode%2010%2C000%20feet%20above%20my%20head...%C2%A0I%20asked%20what%20kind%20of%20protective%20gear%20I%20was%20going%20to%20have%2C%20and%20they%20said%2C%20'Nothing.'%20I%20had%20a%20baseball%20cap%20with%20me%2C%20and%20I%20said%2C%20'I%20better%20wear%20that%20just%20in%20case.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20he%20and%20the%20five%20Air%20Force%20officers%20present%20developed%20cancer%20later%20in%20life%2C%20though%20it's%20unclear%20if%20it%20was%20the%20result%20of%20that%20test%20or%20others.%20Yoshitake%20developed%20stomach%20cancer.%20He%20died%20on%20October%2017%2C%202013%2C%20at%20the%20age%20of%2084%20due%20to%20complications%20from%20a%20stroke.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENPR%20attempted%20to%20tracked%20down%20the%20other%20five%20men%20but%20couldn't%20confirm%20what%20exactly%20happened%20to%20them%20or%20what%20types%20of%20cancers%20they%20may%20have%20developed.%20The%20outlet%20was%20only%20able%20to%20determine%20when%20some%20of%20them%20died.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYoshitake%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2010%2F09%2F14%2Fscience%2F14atom.html%3Fpagewanted%3Dall%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202010%20that%20few%20of%20his%20fellow%20%26quot%3Batomic%20cameraman%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20photographers%20and%20videographers%20who%20documented%20US%20nuke%20tests%20in%20Nevada%20and%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean%20%E2%80%94%20were%20still%20alive%2C%20but%20many%20apparently%20paid%20a%20tragic%20price%20for%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B