tsfile%20for%20Collision%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDemocratic%20lawmakers%20are%20demanding%20a%20Department%20of%20Labor%20investigation%20into%20HR%20startup%20Deel.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20March%2C%20Insider%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-hr-startup-deel-culture-employment-regulatory-2023-2%5C%22%3Ereported%20on%20internal%20concerns%20at%20Deel%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20its%20use%20of%20independent%20contractors.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECalifornia%20rep.%20Adam%20Schiff%20is%20now%20leading%20the%20call%20for%20a%20federal%20investigation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20group%20of%20Democratic%20congresspeople%20led%20by%20California%20representative%20Adam%20Schiff%20are%20calling%20for%20a%20federal%20investigation%20into%20the%20%2412%20billion%20HR%20startup%20Deel%20for%20allegedly%20misclassifying%20employees%20as%20independent%20contractors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20letter%20to%20Acting%20Labor%20Secretary%20Julie%20Su%20on%20July%2026%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-hr-startup-deel-culture-employment-regulatory-2023-2%5C%22%3Eciting%20an%20investigation%20by%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20group%20urged%20the%20United%20States%20Department%20of%20Labor%20to%20investigate%20whether%20Deel%20had%20misclassified%20employees%20as%20independent%20contractors%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fschiff.house.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2Fdeel_letter_to_secsu.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bon%20purpose%20to%20increase%20their%20profitability%20and%20growth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20letter%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-07-26%2Fhr-startup-deel-s-labor-practices-should-be-investigated-lawmakers-say%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20reported%20on%20by%20Bloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider's%20March%202023%20story%20found%20the%20startup%2C%20which%20helps%20large%20organizations%20hire%20and%20manage%20workers%20around%20the%20world%2C%20classified%20at%20least%20half%20of%20its%20workers%20as%20independent%20contractors.%20It%20also%20distinguished%20little%20between%20the%20responsibilities%20of%20full-time%20staff%20and%20independent%20contractors.%20Many%20workers%20told%20Insider%20they%20believed%20they%20were%20applying%20to%20be%20full-time%20employees%2C%20but%20were%20offered%20the%20same%20job%20as%20long-term%20contractors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20startup%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-hr-startup-deel-culture-employment-regulatory-2023-2%5C%22%3Ehired%20workers%20as%20contractors%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Canada%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20Australia%2C%20France%2C%20Germany%2C%20Spain%2C%20Greece%2C%20Brazil%2C%20Turkey%2C%20India%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20Singapore%2C%20the%20Philippines%2C%20and%20Nigeria%2C%20among%20other%20countries.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeel%20workers%20who%20are%20hired%20as%20independent%20contractors%20do%20not%20receive%20certain%20employment%20rights%20that%20they%20would%20otherwise%20be%20entitled%20to%20if%20they%20were%20full-time%20employees.%20Depending%20on%20location%20this%20can%20include%20the%20right%20to%20join%20a%20union%2C%20legal%20protections%20against%20unfair%20or%20sudden%20dismissal%2C%20pension%20contributions%2C%20health%20insurance%2C%20and%20mandatory%20severance%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-conversation%3D%5C%22undefined%5C%22%20data-cards%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20%E2%80%94Adam%20Schiff%20(%40RepAdamSchiff)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fmims%2Fstatuses%2F1684302954109468674%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJuly%2026%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E